article.headline: N. Dakota St. 76, Centenary 60
article.story: FARGO, N.D. -- Mike Felt scored 21 points and TrayVonn Wright added 15 as North Dakota State defeated Centenary 76-60 on Saturday night, the 22nd straight loss for the Gentlemen. All of Felt's 11 shots were from behind the 3-point line, and he made seven to tie a school single-game record. Michael Tveidt had four 3-pointers and scored 13 points for the Bison (9-6, 3-2 Summit League). Jeron Trotman had 12 points for Centenary (0-17, 0-6), which is dropping from Division I to Division III next season. A 14-0 run gave North Dakota State a 30-12 lead. The Bison had a 43-22 cushion at intermission and stretched the lead to 30 in the second half.
